---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Controls from '../components/Controls.astro';
import { site, base } from '../lib/site';

const accents = site.accents;
const h1 = 'method';
---
<Base
  title="enot - method"
  desc="How the palette is built: fixed CIELAB lightness steps, gruvbox hue constraints, simulated dichromacy, a max-min CIEDE2000 optimizer and a regression gate."
  page="method/">
  <div class="hero wrap">
    <h1 style={`--h1ch:${h1.length}`}>{h1}</h1>
    <div class="tail" aria-hidden="true">{accents.map((r) => <i style={`background:var(--${r})`}></i>)}</div>
    <p class="tagline">How the palette is built.</p>
    <p class="sub">The earthy look is a constraint on the optimizer;
    every step below runs again on every build.</p>
    <Controls />
  </div>

  <section><div class="wrap">
    <ol class="method">
      <li>backgrounds and text sit on fixed CIELAB lightness steps;
      accents are optimization variables;</li>
      <li>accents are confined to gruvbox hue sectors and a lightness
      corridor, which together fix the earthy character;</li>
      <li>dichromacy is simulated in linear sRGB: Vienot 1999 for protan
      and deutan, Brettel 1997 for tritan;</li>
      <li>an optimizer maximizes the minimum pairwise CIEDE2000 across
      visions: farthest-point seeding, coordinate ascent, multi-start;</li>
      <li>an aesthetic pass pulls every color back toward its gruvbox
      anchor while the guarantee holds;</li>
      <li>a regression gate re-checks all of it on every build.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="caption">The enforced thresholds are in
    <a href={`${base}numbers/`}>numbers</a>; the papers behind the
    simulation and the distance formula are in
    <a href={`${base}science/`}>science</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <footer><div class="wrap">
    <span><a href={base}>&larr; enot</a> - an earthy colorscheme that survives color blindness.</span>
  </div></footer>
</Base>
